Complete Documentation on all finalized classes and functions

Figure out how to update, fixed update, and late update objects as well
    as how and when to start and awake them

Determine when objects need to be redrawn by checking changes in surfaces if
    it's actually faster to do so

Create a GUI system and figure out some layout/UI effects

State Machine:
    Holds all active Surfaces created or loaded from the Scene Manager
    Send's updates and input to the active State


Rendering:
    A list of active Surfaces held by the current State process updates
    and draws to the Window.
    Window is the base Surface
